heaviest_rainfall.status: Ranked 7th for total rainfall, today's storm had precipitation totalling 23.86mm, falling at 8.3mm per hour at times during the 30.8 hour long storm.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 34.3mm per hour on 02 September 2025, and resulted in 21.19mm of rain over 15.0 hours.  This is the highest rate recorded by our weather station.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 30.8 hours; it delivered 23.86mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  Rain fell for 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 47.89mm with a maximum intensity of 24.6mm per hour.
